I don't think anyone has completed any of the quests yet in new ST, so people are still unsure if there is anything worthwhile there.  They all seem relatively long, though -- collect drops from all across the zone and then hand them in.<br>
<br>
I don't think any guild on FV is ready to take on the new ST and from a pure risk v. reward aspect, there is no reason to do so.  New ST is a lot more work for roughly the same or poorer items.  The only reason to do the wakeup, IMHO, is to see if VI did a new nifty transition script.  If they did, it would be a really fun thing to experience.  Well, the new ST is a fun zone-crawl type of raid, but when I do that much work I like to see nice stuff dropping for people, not &quot;sorry, pass, I have better&quot;.  NTOV is a lot more fun and a lot more rewarding than new ST. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxoraxis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xoraxis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/23/02 4:46:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2773.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Waking the Sleeper</span><hr size=1> VI said that if the sleeper is not awake then the zone will not be changed to the new version.  And my friends on SH say that the new ST is a total waste of time, FYI. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxoraxis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xoraxis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/23/02 4:49:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2773.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Waking the Sleeper</span><hr size=1> &quot;what is the only reason to wake the sleeper?&quot;<br>
